The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Jan. 4: The government has cleared 20 FDI proposals worth Rs 2,791 crore, including one relating to foreign investment of Rs 2,500 crore in Idea Cellular. FIIs, foreign venture capital investors and other entities would raise the foreign investment in Idea Cellular up to 74 per cent.

 Mumbai, Jan. 4: The Reserve Bank today came out with a policy on valuation of properties and appointment of valuers by banks for correctly assessing the cost of the fixed assets. All commercial banks, excluding RRBs, will have to obtain at least two independent valuation reports for properties beyond Rs 50 crore.

 Calcutta, Jan. 4: Nearly 2.5 lakh labourers in Bengals 56-mill jute industry will be on an indefinite strike from Friday, leaders of 22 unions said after the government failed to reach an agreement over their demands. 

 Mumbai, Jan. 4: The board of directors of Bombay Stock Exchange today met here, presumably to discuss its proposed equity sale and an initial public offering to dilute the broker members stake. 

 New Delhi, Jan. 4: The Hero group is entering the electric three-wheeler segment. The group is expected to partner UK-based Ultra Motor, its technical collaborator in electric bicycles and scooters, in its three-wheeler venture.




